<p>Italia '90 gave the world many gifts, but none more joyful than Roger Milla's corner flag celebration. At 38 years old, the Cameroonian striker shimmied and shook at the corner flag with an infectious energy that made the whole world smile. It wasn't just a celebration — it was an announcement that African football had arrived on the global stage with style, charisma, and zero apologies.</p>

